sentences.english: Like marsupial mammals, Hutts nurse their young Huttlets in special brood pouches.
sentences.chinese: 他們像有袋類哺乳動物，在育嬰袋裏撫育幼崽。

sentences.english: The next area to question is the whelping of the puppies.
sentences.chinese: 問題的另一方面就是幼崽的。

sentences.english: We'll post an image of the netherwhelp, offspring of the nether drake flying mount, in the near future.
sentences.chinese: 我們將在捎後放出虛空飛龍幼崽的資料。

sentences.english: Ichthyosaurs and other contemporary viviparous species, by contrast, gave birth to multiple offspring.
sentences.chinese: 相比之下，魚龍和其他現代胎生的物種產下多個幼崽。

sentences.english: A cub is placed into a basket for transportation to a new living environment.
sentences.chinese: 熊貓幼崽被放到一個竹簍裏轉移到新的生活環境。

sentences.english: Now this cat is letting it nurse alongside the rest of her kittens.
sentences.chinese: 現在這隻貓正在照料這隻小熊貓和她其餘的幼崽。

sentences.english: New cubs must be inbred further.
sentences.chinese: 新的幼崽必須進一步近親繁殖。

sentences.english: In this image, a feeder weighs the cub during a physical examination.
sentences.chinese: 這幅圖中，飼養員在體檢過程中給幼崽稱重。

sentences.english: Her young is now exposed and in turn becomes a target.
sentences.chinese: 她的幼崽現在暴露出來，轉而成爲目標。

sentences.english: The researchers perform a physical examination on a panda cub.
sentences.chinese: 研究人員在對一隻熊貓幼崽進行全身檢查。

sentences.english: Cows lactate for up to ten months.
sentences.chinese: 牛可以爲幼崽哺乳10個月。

sentences.english: Mom's trying to teach, but one of her cubs isn't even watching.
sentences.chinese: 媽媽正試着教她們，但是其中一個幼崽卻並沒有在看。

sentences.english: The pinkish object was a baby bushpig.
sentences.chinese: 那個粉紅色的東西原來是一隻野豬幼崽。

sentences.english: The mother tiger gathered her young around her.
sentences.chinese: 母虎把幼崽聚集在它的周圍。

sentences.english: It might even have eaten hatchling or juvenile dinosaurs.
sentences.chinese: 它甚至可能以剛孵出的恐龍或恐龍幼崽爲食。

sentences.english: The 21-day-old male cub was found (dead) yesterday morning.
sentences.chinese: 昨天上午發現這隻出生21天的雄性紅熊貓幼崽死亡。

definition: the young (unborn or newborn) of an animal/larva
liger, hybrid cross between a male lion and a tigress
to give birth (animals)/to bear a litter
tigon or tiglon, hybrid cross between a male tiger and a lioness
